Background Nucleus currently uses Java 21. Issues Nucleus follows the Java cadence and with the release of Java 25, which is an LTS, Nucleus needs to upgrade to Java 25. Before we upgrade to Java 25 we will upgrade all the tools to be ready for Java 25. Changes 1. Changed Gradle to version 9.2.1 2. In AsyncProfiler we are using the lazy execution of the dynamic library instead of non-lazy. This is inline with the new gradle version that moves to lazy APIs. 3. PiTest 3a. Changed the pitest plugin to 1.19.0-rc.2 as it supports Gradle 9. Also changed PiTest to version 1.22 in preparation for the Java 25 upgrade. Moved the group's definition from the Nucleus  build.gradle  to the PiTest.gradle for consolidation of configuration. 3b. In the past, PiTest was set as  shouldRunAfter  the  test  task. However,  shouldRunAfter  is a preference rather than a requirement. ( dependsOn  is required.) With Gradle 9 parallel, PiTest does not run after the  test  task. To overcome this, PiTest depends on the  test  task directly. 4. RuntimeCommandDocs 4a. The class was changed to an abstract class.  4b. The camelCase method was made package private. 4c. In  transitiveDeps  we replace the check for the presence of a  projectDependency  property with (it instanceof ProjectDependency) as the property is not present anymore. We also get the dependency's project from the by inspecting the project corresponding to the dependency's project's path. 4d. With it new strict resolution strategy for parallel builds,  it.dependencyProject.configurations."$cp".files . We are replacing def classpaths = deps.collect {
                configs.collect { config ->
                    def cp = configProperty(config, "compileClasspath")
                    it.dependencyProject.configurations."$cp".files
                }
        }
        String classpathProperty = configProperty(type, 'compileClasspath')
        classpaths.add(project.configurations."$classpathProperty") with String classpathProp…

Background Auctions user is allowed to submit negative limit price if the order's price type is spread. Issues The Auctions Order UI feed allows negative spreads on order submission. However, when the FlexOrderManagerManualSliceWorkflow tries to create an OrderRequestCommand to send the child order, this results in validation error in the MatchingOrderRequestMessageWriter. Currently any validation error in workflow's message writers causes an infinite loop and eventually the workflow bot runs out of memory and crashes. There is a ticket to address the infinite loop issue ( ), however it hasn't been addressed yet. Changes Remove EmptyOrPositiveLongValidator from OrderRequestOrderStipulationsFieldsComposer for limit price Add the following check to MatchingFlexOrderManagerWorkflow.onAssignedWorkflowComplete: if (completionCode == CompletionCode.UNEXPECTED_STATE) {
        shutDown(completionCode);
        return;
    } This will prevent infinite loop from occurring because of a validation failure in auctions-flex-order-manager-bot. Flags This is a bug fix in workflows, it's non-breaking and areas is code.

Background Nucleus uses code generation extensively. Issues Testing generated code is very complex. One can test the XML parser for accuracy, but this does not test the velocity template and eventually the generated code. Alternatively, one can test the generated code but this might not be sufficient because some code paths are missed. There is no perfect solution, but we need some serious improvements. With that in mind, our goal is to test using coverage and preferably check style the generated code. This change does not look for any fixes, but setting up the infrastructure for fixing issues. Changes To achieve our goal we will create a new module named codegen-test. All the test generated code will be generated into this module rather into the codegen module. However, the generated code will be in the main source set. To make the code in the main source set, in the module  build.gradle  we will add sourceSets {
    main {
        java.srcDirs += "<generated code directory>"
... We will copy the unit tests from  codegen  to the  codegen-test  module.  Coverage will happen now automatically. We should start this effort with the generated data classes. We should implement this ticket without making any changes to  codegen  module yet. Flags Area is code as we are developing a new module for testing the generated code. It is not a breaking change because this is a code change making changes to a developer-only API and hence, it does not affect any external users of the system.
